<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,1939,2036]" lastBlockId="22.[151,1437,151,860]" lastPageId="22" lastPageNumber="23" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Stramineous (Plate III: C). Vertex light yellow with six small, dark brown dots on anterior margin, brown longitudinal band midway between eye and midline, eye from brown to dark (Plate III: C); frontoclypeus with fuscous arcs. Pronotum and scutellum stramineous (Plate III: C). Leg marked with dark brown. Forewing light brown, bor- der of cells fuscous (Plate III: C).</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1437,151,860]" box="[197,857,223,247]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Forewing macropterous, inner anteapical cell open basally.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="23" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1437,151,860]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,377,259,284]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Subgenital plate lateral margin slightly convex, apex bluntly rounded (
<figureCitation box="[1196,1280,260,284]" captionStart="FIGURE 21. M" captionStartId="24.[151,250,1587,1610]" captionTargetBox="[222,1353,197,1531]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[188,1398,165,1566]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 21. M. remigia sp. nov. A: male pygofer lobe, lateral view; B: valve, ventral view; C: subgenital plate, ventral view; D: style, dorsal view; E &amp; F: aedeagus and connective, dorsal and lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/206136/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
Fig. 
<number box="[1251,1280,260,284]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" value="21.0">21</number>
</figureCitation>
C); style very long, preapical lobe short and narrow, apophysis digitate, slightly upturned distally (
<figureCitation box="[1106,1189,295,319]" captionStart="FIGURE 21. M" captionStartId="24.[151,250,1587,1610]" captionTargetBox="[222,1353,197,1531]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[188,1398,165,1566]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 21. M. remigia sp. nov. A: male pygofer lobe, lateral view; B: valve, ventral view; C: subgenital plate, ventral view; D: style, dorsal view; E &amp; F: aedeagus and connective, dorsal and lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/206136/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
Fig. 
<number box="[1160,1189,295,319]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" value="21.0">21</number>
</figureCitation>
D); connective lightly longer than aedeagus, aedeagal shaft in lateral view sinuate, slightly broader basally and tapered to obliquely truncate apex (
<figureCitation box="[270,355,367,391]" captionStart="FIGURE 21. M" captionStartId="24.[151,250,1587,1610]" captionTargetBox="[222,1353,197,1531]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[188,1398,165,1566]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 21. M. remigia sp. nov. A: male pygofer lobe, lateral view; B: valve, ventral view; C: subgenital plate, ventral view; D: style, dorsal view; E &amp; F: aedeagus and connective, dorsal and lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/206136/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
Figs 
<number box="[327,355,367,391]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" value="21.0">21</number>
</figureCitation>
E, 
<number box="[386,415,367,391]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" value="21.0">21</number>
F).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1437,151,860]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,401,403,428]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Female genitalia.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[408,464,404,428]" name="India" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Hind</collectingCountry>
margin of seventh sternum with large median U-shape excavation (see Plate IV: F and Plate VI: N).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
